SP.P:
Why this is well: now if I can but hold vp this humor
in him, as it is begun, Caso for Florence, match him & she can;
Come cousin.

Oh its a pretious good foole, make much on him: I
can compare him to nothing more happely, then a Barbers vir∣ginals;
for euery one may play vpon him.

Nay boy, neuer looke askaunce at me for the matter;
ile tell you o it by Gods bread? I, and you and your compa∣nons
mend your selues when I haue done.

What; al this verse, body of me he carries a whole realme;
a common wealth of paper in his hose, lets see some of his
subects.
